ouncil of Undergraduate Research  V CUR  and the Burress and Lanford Scholarship Programs  Other cadets have produced documentaries filmed abroad  Venezuela  Mexico  Guatemala  Nicaragua  and Spain  Still others have chosen a service based project for their independent studies in Spanish  Over the years  cadets have produced training materials for firemen and military personnel  websites for new Spanish speaking residents in Rockbridge Country  a recruiting video for the VMI soccer team   and even a website in Spanish about Croatian military customs      VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 